Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Yiming Liu

2023-03-11

My meme

Once I visited my friends place and saw her cat lying on the sofa, looking very bored. But I still remember how cute he was when he was first adopted. I recalled this scene as hilarious and made it into this meme.

Meme showing

Cat_meme

library(magick)
image_top <- image_read("https://cutewallpaper.org/21x/sxvh0etge/Cute-Baby-Cats-part-2-Steemit.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("300x300!")%>%
  image_annotate("Could you bring me home?",
                 size = 25, 
                 gravity = "southwest",
                 font = "serif",
                 color = "black")

blank_top <- image_blank(width=200, height = 300,color = "white") %>%
  image_annotate("Before adoption...", size = 20, location = geometry_point(25, 130))

meme_top <- image_append(c(blank_top, image_top))

library(magick)
image_bottom <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1055419548625707008/PC1ub3Bk_400x400.jpg")%>%
  image_resize("300x300!")%>%
  image_annotate("Why are you in my house",
                 size = 25, 
                 gravity = "southwest",
                 font = "serif",
                 color = "black")

blank_bottom <- image_blank(width=200, height = 300,color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate("After 3 years...",
                 size = 20,
                 location = geometry_point(30, 130),
                 color = "white")

meme_bottom <- image_append(c(blank_bottom, image_bottom))


meme <- image_append(c(meme_top, meme_bottom),stack = TRUE)%>%
  image_scale(800)%>%
  image_write("my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

Inspiration: I think the pop cat has good conditions to be animated, and I also want to give out a fun feeling like the Snake Game to the audience.

GIF showing

Pop_Cat_Animation

library(magick)
frame <- c(image_read("pop_a.png"),
           image_read("pop_b.png"),
           image_read("pop_c.png"),
           image_read("pop_d.png"),
           image_read("pop_e.png"),
           image_read("pop_f.png"),
           image_read("pop_g.png"),
           image_read("pop_h.png"),
           image_read("pop_i.png"))
animation <- image_animate(frame, fps = 2)

animation %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")
